Digital Marketing Officer (Branding)
Job Highlights
 Oversee digital mkt for Education field, distribution brands 
Multimedia exp with various social media knowhow
 passionate in promoting English education trends
 Digital Marketing training is provided 
Job Description

Job Responsibilities

Formulate digital marketing strategies and plans, including the disciplines of content & paid marketing, including social media, SEO, SEM, website management, advertising, eDM, etc.
Lead integrated digital marketing campaigns from concept to execution
 Brainstorm new and creative growth strategies;
Build brand awareness and increase engagement by developing and designing strong content strategies across digital channels;
Proofread and initiate creative content to ensure it stays on top of trends in English Education field
Perform market and digital analysis, report and generate insights to identify opportunity in the market and support impact decisions;
Set KPIs and implement tracking to evaluate the performance of different digital marketing campaigns through different analytic tools and make recommendations to optimize;
 Plan, execute and measure experiments and conversion tests;
Ad hoc assignments as required.

Job Requirements

Passionate in promoting English Education, knowledge in education field is a plus
Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Multimedia, Communications or related disciplines;
Minimum of 1 years’ digital marketing experience
Multimedia experience is preferred;
Demonstrable experience leading and managing SEO/SEM, marketing database, email, social media and/or display advertising campaigns
Highly creative with experience in identifying target audiences and devising digital campaigns that engage, inform and motivate
Strong analytical skills and data-driven thinking
Well-organized, able to multitasking and cope with fast-paced environment;
Knowledge of the various marketing operations and consumer experiences;
Familiar with Social Media,
Familiar with SEO/SEM, Google Ads and other digital channels;
Good communication and proficient in spoken and written English and Cantonese.
Experience with A/B and multivariate experiments
Solid knowledge of website analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics, NetInsight, Omniture, WebTrends)

Job Responsibilities:
Executive and plan both online and offline events for teachers and students including but not limited to event logistics support and preparation;
Prepare marketing copy for printed and digital campaigns;
Utilize marketing tools to carry out strategic objectives;
Track, analyze and report performance on marketing campaigns;
Provide clerical support to the Marketing team.
Job Requirements:

University degree in Business, Marketing, Multimedia or related discipline;
1-2 years of experience in marketing;
Good command of both Chinese and English;
Knowledge of MS Word, Excel & PowerPoint;
Knowledge of graphics design is a plus;
Good communications and interpersonal skills;
Good coordination and planning skills;
Proactive, well organized, able to work independently and a good team player;
Open mind to learn new skills;
Fresh graduates are also welcome.
We are committed to supporting diversity in our workforce, and ensuring an inclusive environment where all employees can thrive. We seek to employ a workforce representative of the markets that we serve, and encourage applications from people of all ethnic, cultural and social backgrounds.  
Applications, including curriculum vitae, expected salary and work schedule, should be sent by clicking “APPLY NOW”.
Personal data will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Job Highlights 

Solid exp in e-Commerce & Social Media 2-3 years
Work independently for operating an online shop
Knowledge use of web page, photoshop & AI design marketing materials

Job Description

A newly set up on-line shop is looking for a competent, reliable and agile candidate to fill up a position of E-Commence Officer to manage and boost the sales of our  e-Commerce platforms including but not limited to our online shops, to design and prepare marketing materials for both the online shops and showroom.

Duties and Responsibilities

Fully responsible to operate this online shop and showroom independently;
Responsibilities including but not limited to online sales, marketing and daily Operation of this online shop;
Perform & manage operation of this online shop and on different selling channels and  E-Commerce portals; 
Manage daily operations of online shop including generate & update website content (product listing, data entry, promotions, etc);
Effective use of SEO, social media and KOLs to promote our products, e.g. through Facebook, Instagram, Google AD, WeChat group and 小紅書 etc;
Knowledge of video shooting, editing and daily video production;
Analyze and monitor online shop statistics and daily sales data to optimize channel traffic performance and sales; 
Modify weekly product arrangements and make suggestions to change online shop layouts; 
Create & implement tactical offers to support specific products and target specific market;
Other ad-hoc assignments.

Requirements

Degree in Journalism & Communication or related discipline;
2+ year relevant experience in E-commerce platform related, (fresh graduated will be considered);
Possess well-developed design skills and marketing knowledge – capable to use photoshops, AI for design and preparing marketing materials;
Good knowledge of SEO, SEM, Goggle analytics and adwords;
Experience with logistic arrangement and warehouse management is advantage;
Proficient in MS Office (MS Word, Excel, Powerpoint, Outlook);
Capable to work independently;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (include Mandarin).

Availability commencement :

Around February, 2022 (after CNY holiday)

Working days :

5 days per week

Tue–Sat (09:30~18:30); Sun & Mon Rest day

